<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-112-223 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 024 711</DOCID><JOURNAL>Byte  July 1991 v16 n7 p50(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CD-ROM finally becomes affordable. (CDR-1000 disk drive fromTandy/Radio Shack) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Miastkowski, Stan.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Tandy/Radio Shack sells its CDR-1000 disk drive for only $399,about half the price of other CD-ROM drives.andP;  Installation iseasy, taking only 15 minutes.andP;  Inserting CD-ROM disks is performedby hand, rather than mechanically, as in costlier drives.andP;  Nospecial disk cartridges are needed.andP;  The CDR-1000's data transferrate of more than 150 kilobytes per second is more than doublethat of most other CD-ROM drives.andP;  The seek time is a relativelyslow 800 milliseconds.andP;  The data transfer rate is fast in largepart because the CDR-1000 eschews going through the SCSI port andinstead uses a custom interface that delivers data directly to thecomputer's bus.andP;  The CDR-1000 can play music CD's on a properlyequipped computer.andP;  Requirements are an IBM PC with a half-height5.25-inch floppy disk drive bay and an 8-bit add-in slot.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Tandy Corp. Tandy-Radio Shack (Products).andO;Ticker:    TAN.andO;Product:   Tandy CDR-1000 (CD-ROM drive) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionDiscount HardwareDisk drivesCD-ROM.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotographtable.andO;Caption:   The facts. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>